# Project Standards

## Migrations

- **Do not create new migrations** to add, delete, or modify columns on existing tables.
- **Only add migrations** for entirely new tables.
- To change an existing table: **edit the existing migration file**, then run `php artisan migrate:fresh` (or clear cache) and verify.

## Language and locale

- **Comments**: English only.
- **Code/DB**: Field and variable names in English.
- **User-facing strings** (HTML, labels, messages): **Translatable**; supported locales are **Catalan (ca)** and **Spanish / Castellano (es)**. No hardcoded UI strings; use Laravel lang keys or React i18n. See **`.cursor/rules/i18n.mdc`**.
- **Enums** (values shown to users): Store labels in lang files so they translate (e.g. `shop.status.pending` → "Pendent" / "Pendiente").

```php
// ✅ Comment in English; translation key for UI
$table->string('status')->comment('Order status'); // values from lang: shop.status.*
```

## Stack

- **Laravel as API + SPA (React).** Front-end talks to Laravel via **API REST**; React is the default UI. Laravel = backend, API routes, auth. Use **Blade only when necessary** (e.g. HTML shell that loads React, or a single login page if you keep it server-rendered). Do not use Inertia for this project.
- **Auth:** **Custom** (no Breeze). LoginController + session guard, like `~/Repos/abp-app`. See **`.cursor/rules/auth.mdc`**. See also **`.cursor/rules/react-use.mdc`**, **`.cursor/rules/api.mdc`**, **`.cursor/rules/security.mdc`**, **`.cursor/rules/i18n.mdc`**.

## Styling

- Use **Tailwind CSS** for all styling (utility-first, mobile-first). Use **daisyUI** for ready-made components (cards, modals, navbar, etc.); see **`.cursor/rules/daisyui.mdc`** and **`.cursor/rules/tailwind.mdc`**.
- **Form submit buttons:** Place the primary "Save" / "Guardar" button **aligned to the right**. Use `flex justify-end` for the submit row, or `modal-action` in modals (cancel left, save right).
- Put theme tokens and overrides in a global **`styles.css`** (e.g. CSS variables, Tailwind/daisyUI theme). Add a separate CSS file per page or component only when the style does not repeat and is necessary.

## Product variants

- Products can optionally be grouped as **siblings** (variants) via **`product_variant_groups`**. A product belongs to at most one group (`products.variant_group_id`); products in the same group are "brothers" (e.g. same screw 30mm, 40mm, 50mm). No sort column: order variants by name or value in SQL (e.g. `ORDER BY name ASC`). See **`trash/diagramZero.dbml`** for the schema. Model: `ProductVariantGroup`, `Product::variantGroup()`, `Product::variantSiblings()`.

## Shared UI components

- **Page titles:** Use the shared **PageTitle** component (`resources/js/components/PageTitle.jsx`) for the main h1 on every content page (Cart, Orders, Products, Checkout, Profile, etc.). Do not use a raw `<h1 className="...">` for the page heading; keep the same style (bold, tracking-tight, border-bottom) everywhere. See **`.cursor/rules/components.mdc`**.
- Product grids and product tiles use the shared **ProductCard** component (`resources/js/components/ProductCard.jsx`). Use it on the home page (featured) and on the product list page so layout and behaviour stay consistent. See **`.cursor/rules/components.mdc`** for details and other shared components.

## Empty / missing data from the database

- When a field is expected from the API/DB and **nothing is received** (null, undefined, empty), render the field **blank** in the UI.
- **Do not** use placeholders such as em dash ("—"), "N/A", "–", or similar for missing values. Leave the cell or label content empty (e.g. `''` or nothing).

## Page titles

- **Do not** use em dash ("—") as a separator in page titles or in UI text. Use middle dot (" · ") if a separator is needed (e.g. "Edit · Product name").
- **Do not duplicate** in the page title information that is already shown in the page body (e.g. on client ficha, use only "Ficha cliente", not "Ficha cliente · email@example.com", since the email is already in the ficha).

## Admin area

- **Layout:** Admin pages use **AdminLayout** (`resources/js/components/admin/AdminLayout.jsx`): drawer/sidebar, no top header; links to Dashboard, Productes, Característiques, Tipos de característiques, Tornar a la botiga, Logout. All admin routes live under `/admin` and are wrapped by this layout.
- **List pages:** Every admin list (products, features, feature types, packs, admins, etc.) must include:
  - **Page structure:** One row with **PageTitle** only; then one **toolbar row** with search, filters, and (if applicable) the primary "Add" / "Afegir" action. The toolbar must use `flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 sm:gap-4` so the search bar, filter selects, and add button are **on the same row and vertically aligned**. Do not put the add button in a separate row above or below the search.
  - **Toolbar controls:** Use `input-sm sm:input-md` for the search input and `select-sm sm:select-md` for selects so heights align; give the add button `btn-sm sm:btn-md shrink-0`. Use `w-full min-w-0 max-w-xs` (or `max-w-md` where needed) on the search so it doesn't overflow.
  - **Search:** An `input type="search"` with **debounced** value (e.g. 300 ms) sent as query param to the API. Use local state for the input and a separate `searchDebounce` state updated in a `useEffect` with `setTimeout`/`clearTimeout`.
  - **Filters:** Select dropdowns for relevant dimensions (e.g. category, type, active). Send filter values as query params; use empty string for “All” (do not send the param when “All”).
  - **Clickable rows:** Table rows navigate to the edit page on click (and Enter/Space for a11y). Use `role="button"`, `tabIndex={0}`, `onClick` and `onKeyDown`; do not add a separate “Edit” button column unless required.
  - **Table column alignment:** Apply consistent alignment so `th` and `td` in the same column share classes. Use `text-end` for numeric columns (price, stock, counts, totals); add `tabular-nums` on `td` for numeric cells. Use `text-center` for boolean/status columns (is_active, badges). Keep text columns (names, codes, emails) left-aligned (default).
  - **Pagination (admin lists):** When a list is paginated, use a `join` with three elements: prev button, page indicator span, next button. Style: `className="join flex justify-center"` wrapper; prev/next buttons `className="btn join-item btn-sm bg-base-100 border-base-300"`; middle span (not a button) `className="join-item flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-2 h-8 text-sm text-base-content bg-base-100 border border-base-300"`. Use `shop.pagination.prev`, `shop.pagination.page`, `shop.pagination.of`, `shop.pagination.next` for i18n. Do not use `btn-disabled` on the page indicator.
- **CRUD resources:** Products (`admin/products`), Features (`admin/features`), Feature names / types (`admin/feature-names`). Backend: controllers under `App\Http\Controllers\Api\Admin*`; list endpoints accept `search`, `is_active`, and resource-specific filters (e.g. `category_id`, `feature_name_id`). Response shape: `{ success: true, data: [...] }` (and `meta` for paginated lists).
- **i18n:** All admin UI strings use keys under `admin.*` in `resources/js/locales/ca.json` and `es.json` (e.g. `admin.products.title`, `admin.features.search_placeholder`, `admin.feature_types.filter_active`). Reuse `shop.categories.all` for “All” in filters and `common.yes` / `common.no` where appropriate.

## Assets and build

- Use **Vite** for asset compilation (Laravel default). See **`.cursor/rules/vite.mdc`** for entry points. The main app is React; Blade is only for the HTML shell that loads the React bundle when needed.
